cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.CR 

This paper is about person re-identification, which is a computer vision task. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper proposes a novel unsupervised deep framework for person re-identification, which involves learning an unsupervised asymmetric distance metric based on cross-view clustering. This suggests that the paper may also belong to the sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.MM (Multimedia). Finally, the paper also discusses the view-specific bias problem, which is related to the security and privacy of surveillance systems, and may fall under the sub-category of cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
